00:00:12.700 --> 00:00:15.960
DIY Mother's Day Card

00:00:16.120 --> 00:00:18.720
You will need:

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:22.840
Scrapbook Paper

00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:26.860
Ribbon

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:30.960
A Pencil

00:00:31.240 --> 00:00:35.060
A Toothpick

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:39.060
Acrylic Paint

00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:43.320
Scissors

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:47.340
 Hole Punch

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:51.540
Paper patterns (the link to them is in the description)

00:00:51.940 --> 00:00:55.720
Hot Glue Gun

00:00:55.900 --> 00:00:59.860
Trace each paper pattern onto the scrapbook paper, then cut out each piece 

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:03.880
Then, mark the fold line onto the card piece of the scrapbook paper

00:01:33.300 --> 00:01:37.180
Then carefully fold it on the marked fold lines

00:02:07.020 --> 00:02:10.900
Using a toothpick and acrylic paint, make                    dots on the center of the flowers 

00:02:41.960 --> 00:02:45.840
Glue the flower stems to the back of each flower

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:26.180
Arrange the flowers into a "bouquet" inside the card

00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:42.640
Start glueing the "bouquet" together

00:04:08.920 --> 00:04:12.820
Then glue the "bouquet" to the card

00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:47.280
Trim any stems that are too long

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:57.240
Cut out the happy mother's day printout                     (link to this is in the descrition)

00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:07.160
Glue the print out onto the scrapbook paper

00:05:21.300 --> 00:05:25.220
Finally, glue this to the inside of the card

00:05:49.320 --> 00:05:53.200
Use the hole punch to make two (2) holes                    on the front of the card

00:06:23.900 --> 00:06:27.780
Cut a long piece of ribbon and                                  thread it through the holes

00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:42.360
Then tie a bow with the ribbon

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:06.800
That's it!

00:07:17.920 --> 00:07:19.900
Thanks for watching :)

